The Resurchify (38) website (https://www.resurchify.com) contains the criteria for evaluating scientific journals:
✓ Impact score—indicates the number of times documents published in a journal within the past two years have been cited in the current year;
✓ The h-index shows the productivity or impact measure of the journal;
✓ SCImago Journal Rank (SJR) is a metric that ranks journals based on their average prestige per article.Table 3 below summarizes the results of the source analysis.
